UID:WxJePbP1SggluJhCInsXf
SUMMARY:WSMA Math Fair 2026
DTSTAMP:20260317T215405Z
DTSTART:20260329T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:MATH FAIR 2026  \\(Sharing for Elementary & Middle School Famil
	ies\\) Hosted at Eastlake High School\, Sammamish\, WA Join the community 
	for an exciting Math Fair happening on: March 29\, 2026 ⏰ 12:00 PM – 5:00 
	PM 400 228th Ave NE\, Sammamish\, WA 98074 This annual event \\(organized 
	by Washington State Math Association – WSMA\\) brings students together to
	 showcase math projects in a fun\, science-fair–style format. ━━━━━━━━━━━━
	━━━━━━ THEME: Structures & Systems Students explore how mathematical struc
	tures power real-world applications — engineering\, architecture\, compute
	r systems\, and more! ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ COMPETITION DIVISIONS • Grades 3–
	5 • Grades 6–8 Teams of 1–4 students Projects can include trifolds\, poste
	rs\, models\, or demonstrations Awards will be given in each division. ━━━
	━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ HOW TO PARTICIPATE ✔ Submit a team project \\(Grades 3–8\\
	) ✔ Attend and explore projects\, interactive math games & activities ━━━━
	━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ ⏳ IMPORTANT DEADLINES Registration: March 15\, 2026 Project
	 Proposal: March 22\, 2026 Sharing for families who may be interested — th
	is looks like a wonderful opportunity for kids who enjoy building\, design
	ing\, explaining ideas\, and presenting math creatively!\n\nhttps://seatod
	ay.6amcity.com/events/#/details/wsma-math-fair-2026/18305966/2026-03-29T00
	\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning & Education
